Text.LocalizedString: quest set to 2 when you find letter, set to 3 when letter presented to barmaid

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "Clearly God was on my side - or at..."

Text.LocalizedString:
Clearly God was on my side - or at least he wasn't on Belt's - 'cause I can't imagine making it through that pass without the good lord's favour.
The canyon wasn't much to see - same as any canyon I reckon. I scanned the place with my good eye. Almost immediately, I happened upon a campsite in the distant, recently used too - maybe a day, maybe less?

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "The canyon wasn't much to see - sam..."

Text.LocalizedString: The canyon wasn't much to see - same as any canyon I reckon. I scanned the place with my good eye. Almost immediately, I happened upon a campsite in the distant, recently used too - maybe a day, maybe less?

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver (choice): "Search Campsite"

Text.LocalizedString: Search Campsite

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver (choice): "Rest up a while"

Text.LocalizedString: Rest up a while

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "Since there was already a camp here..."

Text.LocalizedString: Since there was already a camp here, I figured I'd take advantage and get some rest.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "There wasn't much to find, but I fo..."

Text.LocalizedString: There wasn't much to find, but I found some burnt scraps in the fire - it was by Belt's hand and no mistake. Couldn't make out much, 'cept for the name 'Reevesville'...

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "Not much else to find there, so I m..."

Text.LocalizedString: Not much else to find there, so I moved on from tryin'.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver (choice): "Leave"

Text.LocalizedString: Leave

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "Cemeteries scattered the land after..."

Text.LocalizedString: Cemeteries scattered the land after the Fall. Soon, bodies piled so high people had to burn 'em instead. Got so bad people didn't even have time to loot 'em all, so there was always the chance of finding something of use - if you could lower yourself to root through the pockets of dead men...

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver (choice): "Lay with the dead a while."

Text.LocalizedString: Lay with the dead a while.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver (choice): "Sully some graves..."

Text.LocalizedString: Sully some graves...

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "I dug around a while, before findin..."

Text.LocalizedString: I dug around a while, before finding myself a rusted gun not dissimilar to my own. I popped it open and found an untapped bullet, which I added to my collection.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "Not much to disturb me here, so I t..."

Text.LocalizedString: Not much to disturb me here, so I threw my head back and got some rest.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver (choice): "Leave"

Text.LocalizedString: Leave

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "I dug around a while, before cuttin..."

Text.LocalizedString: I dug around a while, before cutting my hand on a stray knife. Cut seemed clean, but I figured I'd take a step back from gravediving for a spell.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "Coyote Point... You didn't get..."

Text.LocalizedString:
Coyote Point...
You didn't get to see much pretty in those days, 'cept for places like Coyote Point. Vegetation far as the eye could see - green ones and all. Kill you dead if you eat 'em, mind you.
This place had been a path to down yonder, but the mountain collapse made short work of having that marked off most people's maps.
Still, a nice place to close my eyes for a while and forget about the Fall...

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver (choice): "Rest up a while"

Text.LocalizedString: Rest up a while

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver (choice): "Brave the mountain pass"

Text.LocalizedString: Brave the mountain pass

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "I figured I'd be no good going afte..."

Text.LocalizedString: I figured I'd be no good going after Belt without some rest on me, so I push back my chair, wound down the window and put my feet up on the dash...

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "I knew I had to shave off whatever..."

Text.LocalizedString: I knew I had to shave off whatever time I could in my hunt for Belt, so I made my way through the mountain pass. Made a good go of it too, until some boulders came tumbling down. I hadn't come this far to give up, so I put my foot down and went for it.

Pin.Expression: update.coyote = true; visible.canyon = true; stat.time = stat.time - 1; stat.gas = stat.gas - 5; goto.canyon = true

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver (choice): "Leave"

Text.LocalizedString: Leave

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "I knew I had to shave off whatever..."

Text.LocalizedString: I knew I had to shave off whatever time I could in my hunt for Belt, so I made my way through the mountain pass. Made a good go of it too, until some boulders came tumbling down. I slammed myself into reverse and got away in time to avoid getting crushed, but I didn't come out unscathed...

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Doc Connors: "I was all set to back up the way I..."

Text.LocalizedString:
I was all set to back up the way I came when a young girl comes outta the house and beckons me over. It only when I've pulled up and opened my door that I see the think tubes running from her back into the house. Standing in the doorway is a crooked lookin' old man with a control box in his hands - the doc, I guess.
"Ain't she something? The wonder of pneumatics. Anyway, how can I help?"

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver (choice): "Heal up"

Text.LocalizedString: Heal up

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver (choice): "Buy info"

Text.LocalizedString: Buy info

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver (choice): "Hand over the girl"

Text.LocalizedString: Hand over the girl

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver (choice): "Leave"

Text.LocalizedString: Leave

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "Not much here now, save for two dea..."

Text.LocalizedString: Not much here now, save for two dead bodies - the alive-dead-girl and the twisted man who made her.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Doc Connors: ""Oh, I saw him, friend. He came by..."

Text.LocalizedString: "Oh, I saw him, friend. He came by here not too long ago. Patched him up an sent him on his way - business is business after all. Can't tell you much more than that, save to say he drove off [var=update.direction]-a-ways."

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Doc Connors: "As the girl got out of the car, he..."

Text.LocalizedString:
As the girl got out of the car, he whistled through his teeth.
"Well, that's a shame. I keep telling Mr Radler about contraception, but he insists it mars the experience. Come along now girl."
As he walked passed the automaton, he patted her on the head, "looks like you're going to be a big sister, Marlene."
Radler's girl turned and shot me a pleading look.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver (choice): "Aid her"

Text.LocalizedString: Aid her

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver (choice): "Ignore her"

Text.LocalizedString: Ignore her

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "I could see from the look in her ey..."

Text.LocalizedString:
I could see from the look in her eyes that she knew nothing good was gonna come to her or her baby. No payment was worth that on my conscience. I took out my gun and shot the doc in his back. The I turned the gun on what he'd made of that little girl and put her out of her misery.
Radler's girl thanked me and went through the doc's pockets, taking some keys. She found herself his car and soon she was headed in the direct opposite direction to Radler's place.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "World's a tough place. Never did hu..."

Text.LocalizedString: World's a tough place. Never did hurt to be on a doctor's good side. Sorry girl. I turned away from her. Before I got into my car, I could have sworn the doc's little steam-girl had tears running down her face. been telling myself that's not the case for a long while now.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Doc Connors: "The doc's grin was unnerving when I..."

Text.LocalizedString:
The doc's grin was unnerving when I told him what I wanted. Still, a crazy medic is better than none.
He took me to his surgery and handed me a mask - "breath deep." I took it and hesitated a second, before doin' as he told. Whatever gas he gave me was strong, 'cause soon I was out cold.
When I awoke I felt good, didn't have no stitches in the wrong place either, so I'm guessing I got out with a full compliment of organs.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "I'd seen the signs for Doc Connor's..."

Text.LocalizedString:
I'd seen the signs for Doc Connor's place a while before I took the turn off - and it wasn't long before I started reckonin' that was a bad idea...
Soon as I got near the house, I saw one of those hanging cages - gibbets, I think they're called - with the remains of a young kid inside. I say kid, 'cause I couldn't tell the gender...

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "Getsburg had been a fort back when..."

Text.LocalizedString:
Getsburg had been a fort back when things were going bad. I'd heard tell that locals made special efforts to get inside back then. Seeing those scorched walls and he bones piled up against them, I'm not so sure they were successful...
But that was a long time ago. When I got there it was just a settlement like any other - a shithole filled strange folk with dark pasts, just tryin' get by, one day at a time...

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver (choice): "Buy gas"

Text.LocalizedString: Buy gas

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver (choice): "Buy food"

Text.LocalizedString: Buy food

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver (choice): "Buy some food for the folks back in..."

Text.LocalizedString: Buy some food for the folks back in Rust

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver (choice): "deliver bags"

Text.LocalizedString: deliver bags

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "The pumps were a throwback to this..."

Text.LocalizedString: The pumps were a throwback to this place's military days. Seems the folk here had repurposed a fuel truck. While I was getting a fill, I wondered how they, in turn, filled it - drivin' that any place was a recipe for highway piracy.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver (choice): "I'd a world full of options, but no..."

Text.LocalizedString: I'd a world full of options, but nothing to buy 'em with. I needed to find work and find it fast - Belt wasn't gonna shoot himself, after all...

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Chef: "I joined the locals in what used to..."

Text.LocalizedString: I joined the locals in what used to be the mess hall. The greasy chef behind the counter was pouring something thick and blue into bowls. I decided it was best to not look at the menu and downed it as fast as I could.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Process Girl: "I was directed into an old 'plane h..."

Text.LocalizedString:
I was directed into an old 'plane hangar, the back wall of which was filled with large machines. The woman who greeted me explained that they were the processors that'd turn those bags into food.
Never wanted to see them doin' it. You can eat a lot of things when you don't know how they're made. Takes a real empty belly to unsee that process...

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "I handed over what bullets I could..."

Text.LocalizedString: I handed over what bullets I could spare and was given the food that'd buy. It'll not feed them all, but it'll save a few from going feral for a while.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "I checked around and couldn't find..."

Text.LocalizedString: I checked around and couldn't find anything I could afford. I needed to find more bullets if I wanted to do some good that day...

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver (choice): "Leave"

Text.LocalizedString: Leave

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "A ghost town, no sight of a name an..."

Text.LocalizedString: A ghost town, no sight of a name anywhere. Looked long abandoned. The large black spheres the houses clustered around got me thinking it must have been a factory town. Probably food - from back when food was plentiful enough to sustain some kind of economy.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver (choice): "Search the place"

Text.LocalizedString: Search the place

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver (choice): "Rest"

Text.LocalizedString: Rest

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "Hard to search an entire town, no m..."

Text.LocalizedString: Hard to search an entire town, no matter how small it is. I focused on the main places - the Sherriff's, the Saloon, the post office. Found some undelivered post there, addressed to Denis Fox. Figured I'd drop it to him when passing there next, see if it'd net me some bullets...

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "Been a while since this town had an..."

Text.LocalizedString: Been a while since this town had anyone walk its streets. Decided it was as safe as place as any to heal up a spell.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver (choice): "Leave"

Text.LocalizedString: Leave

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Jeb: "As I pulled up, the station door sw..."

Text.LocalizedString:
As I pulled up, the station door swung open and a small, sick looking man peaked out. I never did find out who he was expected, but when he laid eyes on me, he looked relieved.
"What do you want, kid?" he croaked out. "Gas or food?"

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver (choice): "Buy gas"

Text.LocalizedString: Buy gas

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver (choice): "Buy food"

Text.LocalizedString: Buy food

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Jeb: "I asked the guy for a refill. He st..."

Text.LocalizedString: I asked the guy for a refill. He stared blankly at me, so I guessed I was to do the fillin' myself.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Jeb: "My pit growled out, so I figured I..."

Text.LocalizedString: My pit growled out, so I figured I should get somethin' to eat. The old guy went inside. I heard pots and pans banging a hile, 'fore he came back out and handed me some kinda bread'n'meat concoction. It wasn't tasty, but it did the trick.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver (choice): "Outta bullets..."

Text.LocalizedString: Outta bullets...

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "I delved deep into my pockets, but..."

Text.LocalizedString: I delved deep into my pockets, but I could neither pay nor shoot the man. Nothing for me there, I guessed.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver (choice): "Leave"

Text.LocalizedString: Leave

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver (choice): "Offer to work"

Text.LocalizedString: Offer to work

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Jeb: ""I got work, if you got time." T..."

Text.LocalizedString:
"I got work, if you got time."
Time is one thing I don't have, but I need bullets if I'm going to get my revenge on Belt...
I did a few hours of manual work for him, earned myself a bullet for the trouble.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "Mine - stupid name for a settlement..."

Text.LocalizedString:
Mine - stupid name for a settlement, but I guess they didn't expect to make camp here permanently. Can't recall who first found this stream, but way I hear it, they'd been digging solid for seven years, with new prospectors turning up by the week.
I didn't stay long enough to find the name of the city that had sunken here, but I did gather they were pulling out up to five kilos of plastic bags outta there a day. That's enough to clothe a family or feed three. People used to be so wasteful...
No wonder these folk weren't moving on.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver (choice): "Look around for work"

Text.LocalizedString: Look around for work

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver (choice): "Buy gas"

Text.LocalizedString: Buy gas

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Bag trader: "Once word got around I was askin' a..."

Text.LocalizedString:
Once word got around I was askin' about work, a large and jolly woman with a hole in her face came and found me.
"Bless the winds that sent you! A bolloxing Sandstorm has delayed our normal driver, of all things. Need to get these bags delivered to Getsburg ASAP. You'll get your pay there, and, in case you're thinking it, it'll be easier to take the bullets than to try shift this haul on your own."

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Moron: "A slack-jawed moron ran the pump he..."

Text.LocalizedString: A slack-jawed moron ran the pump here, staring into the sky like I wasn't even there. I filled up, but before I got back in I heard the click of a gun. Lookin' back, I saw the moron had a shotgun trained on me - still staring into the sky like nothin' was happening. Once I put down my bullets, he lifted the gun, his face allthewhile not betraying the exchange that just took place.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver (choice): "Hunt down the deserter"

Text.LocalizedString: Hunt down the deserter

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Escapee: "I got to asking around 'bout that R..."

Text.LocalizedString:
I got to asking around 'bout that Rat. Truth be told, it didn't take long - Rat's a Rat for life, and they're welcome nowhere but Ratland.
A pair a' ugly lookin' twins gleefully led me to the hovel they'd holed themselves up. I stood a tick, waiting for them to scarper, but their ear-to-ear grins told me they were staying put.
I drew my gun and kicked in the door to see a young girl of all things. She was ready. Not for me, I think, just for death in any form. She knew she'd cowarded out and hid too close. Foolish kid.
She started talkin' about her chief and how what they had was something special, "not like those other girls o' his". Yeah, special is only special when you're not asking the wrong kind of questions kid.
She begged me for her life, said she'd make it worth my while.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver (choice): "Shoot her"

Text.LocalizedString: Shoot her

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver (choice): "Let her go"

Text.LocalizedString: Let her go

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Escapee: "Not much out here but your reputati..."

Text.LocalizedString:
Not much out here but your reputation. I needed mine to stay as clean as it could, so I did the job I set out to do.
I did it quick and I did it clean. She'd had a tough life, but at least that was the end of it for her.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Escapee: "I was pretty sure this was gonna be..."

Text.LocalizedString:
I was pretty sure this was gonna be the start of a lot of troubles with the Rats, but her tale mirrored that of Belt and me, so I took a certain type of pity on her.
I didn't do much as let her go. Thinking back, she must'a known from the way I loosely held my gun that she was getting one more chance. Hopefully by the time word got back to the chief, she'd be long gone from this part of the world.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver (choice): "Leave"

Text.LocalizedString: Leave

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "Mole Rats - not even sure they're h..."

Text.LocalizedString:
Mole Rats - not even sure they're human under all the rags. Belt must have made a lot of promises to get through this place alive - and I had nothing to offer.
They lived in old oil lands. Well, not quite. They lived under them - place was scattered with holes, it was. You could see the sun shimmering off the oil - the pits that weren't on fire.
How they lived under there was anyone's guess. None I ever talked to knew how - hell, none I talked to even seen one outside of a fight.
This wasn't a good place to be. It was only a matter of time before they felt the car's vibrations and came topside for meat...

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver (choice): "Offer to do a job for them"

Text.LocalizedString: Offer to do a job for them

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Molerat chief: ""Thzz very fort-naat foor uu. I haz..."

Text.LocalizedString:
"Thzz very fort-naat foor uu. I haz work need done that noot MoolRtz work. Pak haz dezertRR. DezertRR no gud for murale. Uu go, uu kill. Thn ve let past."
I figured killing one Rat had to be easier than killing all these, so I took the job. the chief wasn't the easiest to understand, but I gathered I needed to go to Mine to find their deserter...

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver (choice): "Buy gas"

Text.LocalizedString: Buy gas

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver (choice): "I got your deserter"

Text.LocalizedString: I got your deserter

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver (choice): "Actually, draw your gun"

Text.LocalizedString: Actually, draw your gun

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "The barrens were quiet, but I knew..."

Text.LocalizedString:
The barrens were quiet, but I knew someone soon would come to claim it as their own. Lives would be lost takin' it, more in holdin' it and eventually they'd be run out and somebody new would arrive.
That's just how things were in those days: grabbing land and spilling blood with no aims other than to make it to see one more sunrise.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Molerat chief: "I knew what to look for - we had 'r..."

Text.LocalizedString:
I knew what to look for - we had 'rats back home, after all - so when the oil-pits started flaming up I knew what to expect. They came like demons, appearing from the flames, as if from from hell itself. I got out of the car, arms up high - I'd not survive a fight with them in any measure.
Seeing this, the chief signalled to the others to lower their spears and walked towards me, "vhat bringz uu hereee?"

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver (choice): "Tell the chief that the girl is gon..."

Text.LocalizedString: Tell the chief that the girl is gone

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Molerat chief: ""Uu wantz fool for Uur Kaa?" Wit..."

Text.LocalizedString:
"Uu wantz fool for Uur Kaa?"
With a wave of the chief's hand, three of the smaller pack members dropped to their knees with their faces hovering over the nearest oil-pit.
"How many mootfulz uu want?

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Molerat chief: "If there's ever been a day I was mo..."

Text.LocalizedString:
If there's ever been a day I was more thankful of my fast fingers than this, I don't recall it. I caught them by surprise, dropping three before the first spears had been thrown. Even still I was outnumbered and under armed. Finally, through some good sneaking, clean shots, using their own tools against them and drowning a man in another's burning intestines, it was just me and the chief.
"You kill all dee Rats 'cept dee one I want ded. I'z gone make uu pay." He dived at me, knocking my gun outta my hand. We exchanged blows until eventually my hands somehow ended up around his throat.
As I choked the last bit of life from him, he was still anger incarnate, "I'z gonna haunt uur dreamzzzzzz......."
Truth be told, many nights he did.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver (choice): ""Vell? job done?""

Text.LocalizedString: "Vell? job done?"

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Molerat chief: "I knew this wouldn't go down well,..."

Text.LocalizedString: I knew this wouldn't go down well, but once I told him what had come ot pass, he became furious. I wasn't sure what tongue he was talkin', but I knew they were words of war.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver (choice): "Fight back"

Text.LocalizedString: Fight back

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver (choice): "Run!"

Text.LocalizedString: Run!

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Molerat chief: "I explained that I'd not found thei..."

Text.LocalizedString:
I explained that I'd not found their deserter yet.
"Thn do job!" screamed the chief.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Molerat chief: ""Gud. Now you friend of uz. Pass sa..."

Text.LocalizedString: "Gud. Now you friend of uz. Pass safe heer now. We giiv pay, fool and tell ur prey iz hide to dee [var=update.direction]."

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "I slammed my foot down so hard I'm..."

Text.LocalizedString:
I slammed my foot down so hard I'm sure it near came out the bottom of the car. I got enough of a head start to survive, but enough spears and dragons-breath shells connected to make sure I'd remember that day for a long time.
One thing was for sure, I was never crossing back into Rat territory again.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver (choice): "Leave"

Text.LocalizedString: Leave

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "Reevesville - one of those places y..."

Text.LocalizedString:
Reevesville - one of those places you stay clear of since the Fall. I'm pretty sure there was only one family in that town - one three-hundred-and-something-people large family...
As I pulled into the place, they flooded out of their tents and makeshift homes, fast surrounding my car. They didn't move like you and me - like normal folks. I made sure the door were locked before slightly winding down my window and talking to the first one who didn't seem to be Hyped.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver (choice): "Buy food"

Text.LocalizedString: Buy food

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver (choice): "Buy gas"

Text.LocalizedString: Buy gas

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver (choice): "Buy info"

Text.LocalizedString: Buy info

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Hillbilly: "I kept my exchange short, told 'em..."

Text.LocalizedString: I kept my exchange short, told 'em I needed food. A bundle of leaves was passed up. I opened 'em to find some dark brown greasy lumps. Smelled better than it looked, at least.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Hillbilly: "My translator smiled a toothless gr..."

Text.LocalizedString: My translator smiled a toothless grin and handed me an old milk bottle full of yellow liquid. I hoped it was gas...

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Hillbilly: "I told 'em what I wanted and a ripp..."

Text.LocalizedString: I told 'em what I wanted and a ripple of talk went through the crowd. Word eventually came back that some knew something. They said Belt was [var=update.direction], so I marked what they told me on my map and hoped my bullets were well spent...

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver (choice): "No cash..."

Text.LocalizedString: No cash...

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Hillbilly: "I tried to explain that I had no bu..."

Text.LocalizedString: I tried to explain that I had no bullets, but they didn't understand. They started getting angry and soon they were banging on my car and reaching their hands through the window to get me. Best I could do was rev my engine, put my foot down and plow ahead. Pretty sure I took a few out while I was at it.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver (choice): "Leave"

Text.LocalizedString: Leave

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "I had been driving passed abandoned..."

Text.LocalizedString:
I had been driving passed abandoned crops long before I saw the run-down farm house. I could tell it'd been something back in its day - extensions bolted on hither and yon, near tripled its original size.
As I pulled up out front, a warning shot rang out overhead. I looked up to see a girl - a kid mind you - aiming down from one of the windows, with the biggest rifle I'd seen in a long while.
An old man. Probably - hopefully - a granddaddy, came out. I could tell from his limp he had himself a bio-leg, and that he had long run out of synth for it.
"We don't want no troubles. You get back in that there auto-mobile and drive on off. We don't want no troubles, ya hear?"

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver (choice): "Ask the old man for work"

Text.LocalizedString: Ask the old man for work

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver (choice): "Buy food"

Text.LocalizedString: Buy food

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Old Man Jenkins: "One I explained I just wanted somet..."

Text.LocalizedString:
One I explained I just wanted something to eat, he perked up.
"Don't get much trading these days, always open to making some bullets"
His girl didn't seem to agree and started shouting down from above. couldn't make out what she was saying - it was no language I'd heard of - but I could tell it wasn't welcoming words. The man shouted back up in the same tongue, and seems he overruled her, 'cause I left that place with a full belly.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Old Man Jenkins: "It took a while before he believed..."

Text.LocalizedString: It took a while before he believed me - and even then the girl kept that gun pointed at me until I was long outta sight - but he told me he needed tools and that he'd pay if I got 'em. After I agreed, he told me Rust was the best place to get what he needed.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver (choice): "Leave"

Text.LocalizedString: Leave

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver (choice): "Talk to Jenkins"

Text.LocalizedString: Talk to Jenkins

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Old Man Jenkins: "The old man was sitting on his porc..."

Text.LocalizedString:
The old man was sitting on his porch, rocking back and forth. The girl was upstairs, rifle ever present.
He lifted his hat up from over his eyes, "You get me them tools yet?"
"Not yet," I told him, "but soon."
"Well. Best get back to sleepin' then" and he pulled the hat back down over his eyes.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Old Man Jenkins: "When I showed him the tools he star..."

Text.LocalizedString:
When I showed him the tools he starred in disbelief a while, then threw his hat on the floor and shouted up to the girl, "Hot diggity, he brought them! Put on the stove, we're eatin' tonight!"
Over dinner the girl put a bundle on the table and unwrapped it. Inside were a dozen or so bullets, different shapes and sizes. I found two that'd fit my gun and took 'em. She nodded, put the rest away and carried on eating, never saying a word.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Old Man Jenkins: "I spent an age tryin' to find the o..."

Text.LocalizedString:
I spent an age tryin' to find the old man, but he and the girl were in the barn out back.
When she saw me this time, she half heartedly pointed the gun at me, but I could tell I'd gained her trust.
The old man's legs stuck out from under a harvester of some sort, and there he stayed.
"Shouldn't be long 'fore we can get back to harvesting the land," he called out, his voice made distance by the machine. "Hopefully we'll pull enough good to keep ourselves fed a while. Thanks."

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Radler: "I'd not even shut the car door and..."

Text.LocalizedString:
I'd not even shut the car door and I knew the kinda place Radler's was - fancy-boys and go-go girls started to gather at the windows to see what fresh clientèle was comin' their way.
I could tell quickfast which one was Radler - not leastandall 'cause he was the fat, well-dressed one who's words seems clogged with filth:
"It look-y like some neu cli-on-tell find der way to my esss-tablish-mont. Weelcome - we gotz dee purr-itty bois and dee loose wi-man; enter and take your fancee."

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver (choice): "Buy food"

Text.LocalizedString: Buy food

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver (choice): "Offer to work"

Text.LocalizedString: Offer to work

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver (choice): "Buy info"

Text.LocalizedString: Buy info

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Radler: ""Sure I got work for you." He dr..."

Text.LocalizedString:
"Sure I got work for you."
He dragged a girl outta the crowd and pushed her at me.
"Theese one get herself knocked up. Maybe you bring her to doctor for me, get her de... help she need."

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Radler: ""Sure, sure. My boys fix you up som..."

Text.LocalizedString: "Sure, sure. My boys fix you up sometin real niiice to eat."

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Radler: ""I hear of your friend," Radler tol..."

Text.LocalizedString:
"I hear of your friend," Radler told me.
"Gimme hold of your map and I write it down."
When he handed it back, it said Belt was [var=update.direction] of here.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver (choice): ""You bring back my girl yet?""

Text.LocalizedString: "You bring back my girl yet?"

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Radler: "I told him I'd not taken care of it..."

Text.LocalizedString:
I told him I'd not taken care of it yet.
"Well, hurry up. Whores no make money 'less they on their backs, no?"

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Radler: "I said nothing. He could tell I had..."

Text.LocalizedString:
I said nothing. He could tell I had taken her to Doc Connors.
"Business is cruel, no? but here; your forty coins of silver."

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "I pulled up outside to see the "Rad..."

Text.LocalizedString:
I pulled up outside to see the "Radler's" part of the sign had been removed. I got out of my car and I could see eyes looking out from behind lace curtains, but no door was opening for me.
Not sure how things had turned out here, but one thing was for sure - I was no longer welcome.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver (choice): "Shoot him"

Text.LocalizedString: Shoot him

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "I considered shooting him there and..."

Text.LocalizedString: I considered shooting him there and then, but that'd have put a lot of people out on the street...

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver (choice): "Leave"

Text.LocalizedString: Leave

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "it'd have pained me to let a man li..."

Text.LocalizedString:
it'd have pained me to let a man like Radler live. As he turned away I fired one shot, clean and clear, into the back of his head.
The sound of the bullet would have echoed were it not for the scream drowning it out.
Soon they could see I'd done my killin' for the day and calmed down.
Some seemed happy, others less so. I figured they'd be able to look after their own and didn't stick around to find out otherwise.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver (choice): "Leave"

Text.LocalizedString: Leave

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Radler: ""She's gone", I told him. "Your doc..."

Text.LocalizedString:
"She's gone", I told him. "Your doctor friend's dead too."
He spat on my shoes. "Git out of my sight, dog. And don't bother coming back, hear?"

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver (choice): "Leave"

Text.LocalizedString: Leave

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "Even before I found myself chasing..."

Text.LocalizedString:
Even before I found myself chasing Belt into this part of the world, I'd heard of Rust. Hell, not many places like it.
You ever find yourself wanting to know how the Fall came to be, you take yourself on over to Rust. What you see there will wash tales from your eyes and make things clearer than clear.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver (choice): "Buy gas"

Text.LocalizedString: Buy gas

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver (choice): "Do some care work"

Text.LocalizedString: Do some care work

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "I looked about the place, seeing a..."

Text.LocalizedString:
I looked about the place, seeing a lot of sick folk and mech-limbs. Place like this can't sustain these numbers, but none can afford to get out - no place else would have 'em anyways.
I took a look at some food wrappers blowin' by my feet - seems it was coming from Getsburg. Maybe if I pass that way, I'll pick up some food to drop back here.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver (choice): "Ask around for tools"

Text.LocalizedString: Ask around for tools

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Tool seller: "A rebreather altered voice (couldn'..."

Text.LocalizedString: A rebreather altered voice (couldn't tell if it was a man or woman) said they could help me out, if I had the cash to pay.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver (choice): "Buy the tools"

Text.LocalizedString: Buy the tools

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver (choice): "Decline"

Text.LocalizedString: Decline

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Tool seller: "I ain't got the cash to go solvin'..."

Text.LocalizedString: I ain't got the cash to go solvin' other people's woes...

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Tool seller: "I handed over the bullets and got t..."

Text.LocalizedString: I handed over the bullets and got the tools the old man was needin.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Gaskids: "I was pointed to a part of town tha..."

Text.LocalizedString: I was pointed to a part of town that was just made from the shells of cars. There, children spent their days suckin' gas outta tanks and spitting it into buckets. Picked myself up what I needed and gave the nearest kid a coin, hopin' I'd never have to come back here again.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver (choice): "Distribute food"

Text.LocalizedString: Distribute food

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "At first the people seemed suspicio..."

Text.LocalizedString:
At first the people seemed suspicious of me, but soon their hunger got the better of them and they started grabbing food blocks. Thankfully there was enough to go around.
As I was getting back into my car, a woman came over and told me she'd heard I was looking for Belt. I said I was and she told me he'd last been seen in the [var=update.direction]. Then she handed me a canister of NOx and disappeared into the crowd.
I guess good deeds don't always go unrewarded...

Pin.Expression: update.info = true; Item["ifood"].Count = 0; stat.gas = stat.gas + 10; Quest["food"].State = 5

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver (choice): "Leave"

Text.LocalizedString: Leave

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "Should be able to get some gas and..."

Text.LocalizedString: Should be able to get some gas and food here...

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "Seems like a place to get info..."

Text.LocalizedString: Seems like a place to get info...

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "Empty as a barren womb, Should be a..."

Text.LocalizedString: Empty as a barren womb, Should be able to rest up a while.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "A medic - could be good for some he..."

Text.LocalizedString: A medic - could be good for some healin'

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "A canyon, ain't that different to a..."

Text.LocalizedString: A canyon, ain't that different to any other.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "A family town with a family enterpr..."

Text.LocalizedString: A family town with a family enterprise. And that enterprise is inbreedin'.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "A burnt out husk of a town. Should..."

Text.LocalizedString: A burnt out husk of a town. Should be a fun visit...

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "An old ranch. Not sure what to expe..."

Text.LocalizedString: An old ranch. Not sure what to expect.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "Mole Rat turf - nothing good comes..."

Text.LocalizedString: Mole Rat turf - nothing good comes from bein' found here.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "A piece of bliss in this desert hel..."

Text.LocalizedString: A piece of bliss in this desert hell.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "A military fort turned town."

Text.LocalizedString: A military fort turned town.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "A remote saloon."

Text.LocalizedString: A remote saloon.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "A whole heap of dead folk"

Text.LocalizedString: A whole heap of dead folk

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "A shanty-town turned settlement"

Text.LocalizedString: A shanty-town turned settlement

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "An abandoned town. Maybe good for a..."

Text.LocalizedString: An abandoned town. Maybe good for a rest.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "<color=white>I sat next to him and..."

Text.LocalizedString: <color=white>I sat next to him and waited until he was distracted by his drink. I slowly moved my hand towards his row of bullets.</color>

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver (choice): "Steal his bullets"

Text.LocalizedString: Steal his bullets

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "Sitting before the old man was a li..."

Text.LocalizedString: Sitting before the old man was a line of pristine bullets, all of which woulda worked in my gun...

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver (choice): "Leave the bullets where they are"

Text.LocalizedString: Leave the bullets where they are

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "<color=white>Wanting those bullets..."

Text.LocalizedString: <color=white>Wanting those bullets wasn't reason enough to rob an old and blind man. At least not for now, it wasn't.</color>

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Blind man: ""Don't come no closer, you young cu..."

Text.LocalizedString: "Don't come no closer, you young cus. Just cause I's not able to see you, don't mean I be hearing nought."

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: ""Sorry old timer. Dog eat dog world..."

Text.LocalizedString: "Sorry old timer. Dog eat dog world and all that."

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Blind man: "<color=white>The old man snorted, <..."

Text.LocalizedString: <color=white>The old man snorted, </color>"and I thought it was bad bein' old before the Fall..."

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "<color=white>I don't know why, but..."

Text.LocalizedString: <color=white>I don't know why, but something about what he said give me the guilt. </color>"Maybe I can do something for you? To make things right between us?"

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Blind man: "<color=white>He thought for a while..."

Text.LocalizedString: <color=white>He thought for a while,</color> "I sure would like to smell me some of those Oasis Roses one last time..."

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "<color=white>I'd already brushed wi..."

Text.LocalizedString: <color=white>I'd already brushed with my conscience on this matter and wasn't willing to do it again.<color>

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Blind man: ""Thanks again, kid. Smells real nic..."

Text.LocalizedString: "Thanks again, kid. Smells real nice."

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Blind man: ""You get that flower for me yet?""

Text.LocalizedString: "You get that flower for me yet?"

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Blind man: ""Here you go old timer.""

Text.LocalizedString: "Here you go old timer."

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Blind man: "...hiccup..."

Text.LocalizedString: ...hiccup...

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: ""Not yet old timer. Working on it,..."

Text.LocalizedString: "Not yet old timer. Working on it, though."

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "His fingers, thin and knobbled, fum..."

Text.LocalizedString:
His fingers, thin and knobbled, fumbled about in front of him for the flower. When I handed it over, he gave it a powerful sniff. I thought for a moment he forgot I was there but, without a word, he slid three bullets in my direction.
Wasn't expecting to get paid, but I took 'em, nonetheless.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "<color=white>Saloon? Not sure I'd h..."

Text.LocalizedString:
<color=white>Saloon? Not sure I'd have called Fox's a Saloon. Four dirt walls holding up a patchwork tin roof would be a truer - if less kind - description. The smell of homebrew'd liquor was strong here - I guessed that was to mask the smell of the locals...
An old miner sat at the bar, his spice-blinded purple eyes starred ahead. Occasionally he took a sad sip from his mug. A row of bullets was lined up in front of him and he knocked one down each time he wanted a refill.
There was a guy playing pool in that half-hearted way that let people know if they wanted trouble, he'd kindly give it to them.
The barmaid was cute - the kind of cute that loosens lips. If there was info to get here, she was the one to get it from.</color>

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "<color=white>Not much changed since..."

Text.LocalizedString:
<color=white>Not much changed since last I was here.
The barmaid was still flirting, the old man was still drinking and the guy playing pool gave the place a stink o'trouble. </color>

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "<color=white>I asked to see Fox. Th..."

Text.LocalizedString: <color=white>I asked to see Fox. The barmaid wanted to know why, so I showed her the letter, figured it was my duty to make she it got to where it had to go. </color>

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Pool Shark: "<color=white>She wasn't buying it...."

Text.LocalizedString: <color=white>She wasn't buying it. Then the pool shark, talking into a comms device of some sort, piped up,</color> "where's this letter from?"

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "<color=white>Figured he was speakin..."

Text.LocalizedString: <color=white>Figured he was speaking for Fox, so without skipping a beat (or turning to face him) I explained I'd found it in an old town not far from here. </color>

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Pool Shark: "<color=white>Silence for a moment...."

Text.LocalizedString:
<color=white>Silence for a moment. Not my first rodeo, so I could tell he had a gun aimed at me.
There was some mumbling - likley him on his device - before he said me, </color> "Basement".

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "<color=white>I wasn't all that keen..."

Text.LocalizedString: <color=white>I wasn't all that keen on going down there, but I figured I had two choices, go myself or be taken down in less friendly circumstances.</color>

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "<color=white>Hear a lot of rumours..."

Text.LocalizedString: <color=white>Hear a lot of rumours about Fox. Kind a' rumours that'd leave you thinking dirt wasn't the only thing under this shack.</color>

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "<color=white>I had no urge to talk..."

Text.LocalizedString: <color=white>I had no urge to talk to the man, but he seemed the sort to know what I wanted to know,</color> "Where's the nearest cathouse?"

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "<color=white>He played pool in that..."

Text.LocalizedString: <color=white>He played pool in that unfocused, constantly-scanning-the-room manner that let anyone paying attention know that if they started trouble, he'd be of a mind to end it.</color>

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Pool Shark: ""Whut you starin' at?""

Text.LocalizedString: "Whut you starin' at?"

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver (choice): "Don't shoot him"

Text.LocalizedString: Don't shoot him

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "<color=white>I had no quarrel with..."

Text.LocalizedString: <color=white>I had no quarrel with the man, so I opted to not let his attitude get to me and kept on walking.</color>

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver (choice): "Shoot him"

Text.LocalizedString: Shoot him

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver (choice): "Quarrel or not, I had no bullets on..."

Text.LocalizedString: Quarrel or not, I had no bullets on me, so I opted to walk away before thing became something I wasn't ready for.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "<color=white>His tone was upsetting..."

Text.LocalizedString: <color=white>His tone was upsetting to me, so I did what you do out here and drew my gun.</white>

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Pool Shark: "<color=white>He eyed me up and down..."

Text.LocalizedString: <color=white>He eyed me up and down a minute before answering.</color> "You want Radlers," <color=white> is all he said, but it was enough for me.</color>

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: ""Wanted: dead or alive - Mundo Garc..."

Text.LocalizedString: "Wanted: dead or alive - Mundo Garcia for crimes too innumerable and heinous to list - Bounty five bullets."

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver (choice): "I need the bullets, I'll try find h..."

Text.LocalizedString: I need the bullets, I'll try find him.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver (choice): "I don't have time for this."

Text.LocalizedString: I don't have time for this.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "<color=white>Says here he's fond of..."

Text.LocalizedString: <color=white>Says here he's fond of cathouses. Maybe I can ask about for the local one?</color>

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "<color=white>Maybe I'll come back t..."

Text.LocalizedString: <color=white>Maybe I'll come back to this once I've taken care of Belt.</color>

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Barmaid: ""I can help... For a price...""

Text.LocalizedString: "I can help... For a price..."

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver (choice): ""Sure, but it better be worth it...""

Text.LocalizedString: "Sure, but it better be worth it..."

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver (choice): ""Forget it.""

Text.LocalizedString: "Forget it."

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Barmaid: ""He went [var=update.direction] of..."

Text.LocalizedString: "He went [var=update.direction] of here," <color=white>she said and I updated my map.</color>

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Barmaid: ""Suit yourself sugah," <color=white..."

Text.LocalizedString: "Suit yourself sugah," <color=white>she said before going back to pouring drinks.</color>

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: ""I'm looking for some information.""

Text.LocalizedString: "I'm looking for some information."

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Barmaid: ""Can I help you sugah?""

Text.LocalizedString: "Can I help you sugah?"

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver (choice): ""I'm looking for a cat house.""

Text.LocalizedString: "I'm looking for a cat house."

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Barmaid: ""That's not the kind of thing I can..."

Text.LocalizedString: "That's not the kind of thing I can help with, I'm afraid."

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "<color=white>Where that door led to..."

Text.LocalizedString: <color=white>Where that door led to was unclear, but the smell and moans coming from it made me think I was better off not knowing.</color>

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "<color=white>I'd be down there once..."

Text.LocalizedString: <color=white>I'd be down there once, and that was one time too many.</color>

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: ""I've no urge to cause offence, but..."

Text.LocalizedString: "I've no urge to cause offence, but I've done my bit for kindness and ain't interested in getting sidetracked any longer. I've got me a man to kill."

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver (choice): "Ask for food"

Text.LocalizedString: Ask for food

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver (choice): "Ask for info on Belt"

Text.LocalizedString: Ask for info on Belt

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver (choice): "Ask for bullets"

Text.LocalizedString: Ask for bullets

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver (choice): "Ask for gas"

Text.LocalizedString: Ask for gas

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Denise Fox: ""Gas it is. And thanks for bringing..."

Text.LocalizedString: "Gas it is. And thanks for bringing me this. reminds me of a kinder time."

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Denise Fox: ""I'm sure I can have something must..."

Text.LocalizedString: "I'm sure I can have something mustered up for you. I'll tell them to make sure they use the good meat - the real stuff. Thanks for bringing this letter to me; reminds me of a kinder world."

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Denise Fox: ""Info it is; what's this person go..."

Text.LocalizedString: "Info it is; what's this person go by?"

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Denise Fox: "<color=white>She pulled a gun from..."

Text.LocalizedString: <color=white>She pulled a gun from her belt and popped out a few of the bullets.</color> "Here you go, though I hope you won't need 'em. Thanks for bringing me my letter. Not much acts of kindness since the fall."

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver (choice): "Ask for medical help"

Text.LocalizedString: Ask for medical help

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Denise Fox: ""I can have one of my guys clean yo..."

Text.LocalizedString: "I can have one of my guys clean you up, sure. Just head on upstairs and they'll see to you."<color=white> I tipped my hat and turned to leave.</color>

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "<color=white>As I descended the sta..."

Text.LocalizedString: <color=white>As I descended the stairs, I could smell cigar smoke and burning meat, among other things.<color>

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "<color=white>As I entered the room,..."

Text.LocalizedString: <color=white>As I entered the room, I saw a woman with hammer over her shoulder. She stood over some poor guy who was tied to a chair and looked worse for wear.<color>

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Denise Fox: ""You have something for me?""

Text.LocalizedString: "You have something for me?"

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: ""You fox?""

Text.LocalizedString: "You fox?"

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Denise Fox: "<color=white>Silence for a second.<..."

Text.LocalizedString: <color=white>Silence for a second.</color> "Guessing if I ain't, you're gonna tell me you won't hand that there letter over?"

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "<color=white>She didn't look at me...."

Text.LocalizedString: <color=white>She didn't look at me. She kept her gaze fixed on the poor mook beneath her, as she put out her cigar on him.</color>

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Victim: ""Argh! Please stop! I don't have no..."

Text.LocalizedString: "Argh! Please stop! I don't have nothing to tell ya!"

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "<color=white>I waited until the guy..."

Text.LocalizedString: <color=white>I waited until the guy stopped snivelling.</color> "Well. I'd put up a fight, anyhow."

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "<color = white>Silence once more. T..."

Text.LocalizedString: <color = white>Silence once more. Then laughter.</color>

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Denise Fox: ""You're all right. I'm Denise Fox,..."

Text.LocalizedString: "You're all right. I'm Denise Fox, this here is my watering hole."

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "<color = white>I handed over the le..."

Text.LocalizedString: <color = white>I handed over the letter.</color>

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Denise Fox: "<color=white>She paused for a momen..."

Text.LocalizedString:
<color=white>She paused for a moment.</white>
"Well then. You just tell me how I can help you end him and I'll do my bit of kindness in return."

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Denise Fox: "<color=white>She nodded at the man,..."

Text.LocalizedString:
<color=white>She nodded at the man, semi-conscious on the chair.</white>
"Let me finish up my business here then you and I can head upstairs for a drink."

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: ""Belt Dalton.""

Text.LocalizedString: "Belt Dalton."

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Denise Fox: ""Belt Dalton? Glad to hear he's fin..."

Text.LocalizedString: "Belt Dalton? Glad to hear he's finally going to get what's coming to him. Way I hear it, he's hiding out [var=update.direction] of here, waiting for his brothers to show up."

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Denise Fox: ""If that's true you'll want to get..."

Text.LocalizedString: "If that's true you'll want to get to him 'fore they do. Good luck. And thanks for bringing me this. reminds me of a kinder time."

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Denise Fox: "<color=white>She called out to me a..."

Text.LocalizedString: <color=white>She called out to me as I started back up the stairs</color>"And hey - thanks for bringing me this. Many's a folk'd tried to hold this over me - not that it'd have worked. I appreciate the kindness, though."

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "The flower for my blind friend. Mig..."

Text.LocalizedString: The flower for my blind friend. Mighty powerful smell to it.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "An old map of the area. Ain't got a..."

Text.LocalizedString: An old map of the area. Ain't got any post-Fall places on it, so filling them in as I go.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "I hope this ain't a bill..."

Text.LocalizedString: I hope this ain't a bill...

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "Three kilos of plastic bags - if I..."

Text.LocalizedString: Three kilos of plastic bags - if I wasn't so set on gettin' Belt, I could'a drove off and started a new life...

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "Not sure exactly what food was in t..."

Text.LocalizedString: Not sure exactly what food was in that box. Sealed so tight I couldn't even steal a slice.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "She didn't speak to me, even when I..."

Text.LocalizedString: She didn't speak to me, even when I tried. I hope she's okay.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "Gathering o' spare parts. Could alm..."

Text.LocalizedString: Gathering o' spare parts. Could almost use these myself...

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "Mundo Garcia, wanted dead or alive...."

Text.LocalizedString: Mundo Garcia, wanted dead or alive. Bounty is five bullets, location - some cathouse.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "A six-shooter. More damage than a d..."

Text.LocalizedString: A six-shooter. More damage than a derringer, more concealable than a shotgun.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "It took me some driving, but I even..."

Text.LocalizedString:
It took me some driving, but I eventually found somewhere nice to rest my head. Clear water, sand - even the remains of a palm tree.
Water looked good enough to drink - not that anyone's foolish enough to drink water these days.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver (choice): "Put your feet up a while"

Text.LocalizedString: Put your feet up a while

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver (choice): "Look for that flower"

Text.LocalizedString: Look for that flower

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "Figured I'd be true to my word and..."

Text.LocalizedString:
Figured I'd be true to my word and hunt down the old guy's flower.
Took me some time - pleasant time, mind you - but I got that I figured was it.
At least, it was the most pungent flower around...

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "This place seemed pretty empty. Fig..."

Text.LocalizedString: This place seemed pretty empty. Figured I'd catch up on some Zs while I could.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver (choice): "Leave"

Text.LocalizedString: Leave

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Belt: "Ouch!"

Text.LocalizedString: Ouch!

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Belt: "Gah!"

Text.LocalizedString: Gah!

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Belt: "Urgh!"

Text.LocalizedString: Urgh!

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "Ack!"

Text.LocalizedString: Ack!

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "Ugh!"

Text.LocalizedString: Ugh!

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "Oophm!"

Text.LocalizedString: Oophm!

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Belt: "Mara? Thought you were dead."

Text.LocalizedString: Mara? Thought you were dead.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "Takes more than a few gut shots to..."

Text.LocalizedString: Takes more than a few gut shots to take me out.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "You shouldn't have crossed me like..."

Text.LocalizedString: You shouldn't have crossed me like that. I mean to finish what you started, Belt

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Belt: "We'll see about that."

Text.LocalizedString: We'll see about that.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Belt: "So I see. Shoulda put one in your h..."

Text.LocalizedString: So I see. Shoulda put one in your head. Sentimental of me to want to give you an open casket.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "I woke with a gasp."

Text.LocalizedString: I woke with a gasp.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "Taste of copper in my mouth."

Text.LocalizedString: Taste of copper in my mouth.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "Everything was black."

Text.LocalizedString: Everything was black.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "Then the pain hit, like a car rammi..."

Text.LocalizedString: Then the pain hit, like a car ramming into my chest.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "Two shots, right in the gut."

Text.LocalizedString: Two shots, right in the gut.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "Belt had betrayed me."

Text.LocalizedString: Belt had betrayed me.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "Left me die in the desert."

Text.LocalizedString: Left me die in the desert.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "He took the cache and ran."

Text.LocalizedString: He took the cache and ran.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "Didn't know how much life I had in..."

Text.LocalizedString: Didn't know how much life I had in me.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "But I could hear my car still runni..."

Text.LocalizedString: But I could hear my car still running.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "He was meeting his brothers Friday..."

Text.LocalizedString: He was meeting his brothers Friday at high noon.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "I couldn't outshoot them all."

Text.LocalizedString: I couldn't outshoot them all.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Driver: "If I wanted my revenge, wounds or n..."

Text.LocalizedString: If I wanted my revenge, wounds or not, I had to start after him now.
